quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  43,46,"We sent Moses with Our signs to Pharaoh and his chiefs. He said to them: \"I am a Messenger of the Lord of the worlds"
  43,47,"When he showed them Our signs, they laughed at those signs"
  43,48,"Yet We showed them sign after sign each greater than the one preceding it and We afflicted them with the scourge, so that they might return to the Right Way"
  43,49,"Each time they were seized by a scourge, they requested Moses: \"O magician! Pray to your Lord for us by virtue of the covenant He has made with you; we shall surely accept your guidance"
  43,50,"But each time We lifted the scourge from them, they broke their pledge"
  43,51,"One day Pharoah made a proclamation among his people: \"O my people! Is not the kingdom of Egypt mine? Are not these rivers flowing beneath me? Can you not see"
  43,52,"Am I not better than this despicable wretch, who can hardly express himself clearly"
  43,53,"Why have no gold bracelets been given to him, or angels sent down to accompany him"
  43,54,Thus did he incite his people and they obeyed him; surely they were a nation of transgressors
  43,55,"At last when they provoked Us, We inflicted retribution on them and drowned them all"
  43,56,and made them a lesson and an example for the later generations